Golems are creatures created by powerful magic-users using the spell
\emph{artificial life}. Since they are close to animated objects, they
are \textbf{immune to arrows}, \textbf{immune to poison} and
\textbf{immune to most spells}: they still stumble on a slippery slope
and they still burn if they are made of straw or wood, so some
adjudication is required.

All golems are large and strong. They often act as sleepless
guardians, tireless porters and fearless protectors. And since they
don't die, they keep following the orders of their long dead masters.

\begin{quote}
