Manticores are bitter old men that turned into monsters: haters are
going to hate and the most bitter haters are transformed into
lion-like creatures with dragon wings and a spiked tail. Manticores
keep their old, bearded human faces but the hair grows wild and the
jaws grow stronger. These bitter old men just keep on hating: they
hate the spikes regrowing like shark teeth, they hate their old towers
fallen to ruin, they hate the villagers, they hate pilgrims, they hate
everybody. And now they have the body act upon it.

They can let fly up to six \textbf{spikes} per round, shooting them at
anybody within \SI{60}{ft}. They have 24 spikes and thus they can keep
this up for four rounds.

\begin{quote}
HD~6+1 AC~16 1d6/1d6/1d10 or \emph{spikes} F6 MV~18 ML~9
XP~600
\end{quote}

\textbf{Numbers}: 1. They are sometimes found in the company of a
\hyperref[sec:hobgoblin]{hobgoblin} army.

\textbf{Names}: Old Man Pain, Old Man Greed, Old Spite, Lord Envy,
Grandfather Hate, Avarice.

\robber Whoever travels alone is their prey: villagers or witches,
pilgrims or traveling knights.

