Nixies are beautiful water people. If they want, anybody hearing them
talk, sing, or play an instrument must save vs.~spells or be
\textbf{charmed}. Usually victims are drawn to follow the nixies into
the water and spend weeks and months below the surface in their
company, entertaining and serving them. The kiss of a nixie grants
their victims the ability to breathe under water for a day.

\begin{quote}
HD~1 AC~13 1d4 F1 MV~12 ML~6 XP~100; \emph{charm}, \emph{water breathing}
\end{quote}

\textbf{Spells}: Their have the natural ability to cast spells and can
teach them to you, for a price.

\emph{Charm person} (1\st circle) turns one humanoid creature into a
loyal friend. Note that undead and giants may be humanoid but they're
still immune to this charm. The target is granted a saving throw
vs.~spells.\marginnote{As time passes, more saving throws are granted
