\section{Ogre}
\label{sec:ogre}
\index{Ogre}
\caves{Ogre}
\mountains{Ogre}
\begin{marginfigure}
  \includegraphics{Ogre.jpg}
\end{marginfigure}

An ogre is a human that has suffered prolonged exposure to Earth Blood.
Magic has mutated them, making them stronger, larger and even more
violent. They can be up to twice as big as humans.

\begin{quote}
HD~4+1 AC~15 1d10 F4 MV~9 ML~10 XP~400
\end{quote}

Some ogres master the magic of wind and mountain,
turning into an \textbf{ogre mage}. They use magical \textbf{fog}
to set an ambush with their allies and they remain
\textbf{invisible} until they are ready to deal the death blow. This
usually involves sneaking up on their enemies and unleashing a
\textbf{snow storm}. In a fight, their weapons burst into
\textbf{flames}, dealing extra damage.

\begin{quote}
HD~6+1 AC~15 1d10 + 1d6 \emph{fire} F6 MV~9 ML~10 XP~600; \emph{fog},
\emph{invisibility}, \emph{snow storm} 3×/day for 6d6 damage up to
\SI{30}{ft}
\end{quote}

\textbf{Spells}: An ogre mage can teach you their spells, for a price.

\emph{Flaming Weapon} (3\rd circle) lets you shoot flaming arrows or
have your melee weapon burst into flames, dealing an extra 1d6 of fire
damage.

\emph{Fog} (2\st circle) summons forth a supernatural fog that spreads
in all directions for \SI{1}{h/level}, limiting sight to a few feet.
Within the fog, ranged attacks and all spells that require a visible
target are therefore limited to a range of but a few feet. This also
works underground and within buildings.

\emph{Invisibility} (2\nd circle) makes you invisible until you attack
a living creature.

\emph{Snow Storm} (3\rd circle) deals 1d6/level of cold damage, save
vs.~spells for half.

\textbf{Numbers}: 1d6. Ogres are often seen in the company of
\hyperref[sec:orc]{orcs}. When meeting ogres, there's a 1 in 6 chance
of them being led by an ogre mage.

\textbf{Names}: Pain. Smash. Club. Hammer. Rock.

\robber These are the treasures of their victims.

\textbf{Terrain}: caves, mountains.



